<tr valign="top" height="400" >
<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; bEditID:r3st1; color:#000000; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<div style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style="font-size: 12pt;">Hi {!Contact.FirstName},<br><br>Thanks for getting in touch with Kingsbridge.<br><br>We are writing to confirm that, as per your request,&nbsp;<b>we have cancelled your insurance policy&nbsp;<i>(insert policy number)</i>&nbsp;</b>with Kingsbridge.<br><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br>To confirm,&nbsp;<b>your policy was active for the period (DDMMYYYY to DDMMYYYY)</b>.</span></div><div><br><b style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>Cancelling your payment<br></b><i style="font-size: 12pt;"><br></i><div><font face="arial">Since you were paying for your policy via Direct Debit, we have contacted Close Brothers to cancel your direct debit as of the above date. They will write to you with confirmation of this. Please rest assured that no further payments are due for this policy.</font></div><div><font face="arial"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial">&nbsp;As a payment is currently in progress, we need to wait until this is completed before processing your refund. This refund will be credited to the account from which you made your Direct Debit payments within 10 to 15 working days.</font></div><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br><b>Making a claim<br></b></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><b><br></b><u>Any claims submitted for the Professional Indemnity and Directors’ and Officers’ elements of the policy cannot be met as these operate on a ‘claims made’ basis</u></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">, meaning the policy must be active to respond.<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>However, any claims for the Personal Accident, Public Liability, and Employers’ Liability elements for the time your policy was active</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;can still be notified to insurers. Please refer to your&nbsp;<a href="https://www.kingsbridge.co.uk/policy-documents/">policy wording</a>&nbsp;for full details.<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br><i>(Use if for IR35 Add On)</i></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;IR35 Protect operates on a ‘claims made’ basis, so the policy must be active to respond to most claims. However, for&nbsp;<a href="https://www.kingsbridge.co.uk/policy-documents/">sections 10-12</a>&nbsp;on your policy there is a 4-year extended reporting period for you to notify us of a claim for an investigation during the period your policy was active</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">. Any claim in these sections must be notified to insurers within 30 days of an insured event taking place and before any response to HMRC. Your appointed representation will work with you to respond and manage communications with HMRC.<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br><i>(Use for Legal Expenses)</i></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;Legal Expenses cover operates on a ‘claims made’ basis and therefore the policy must be live in order to respond in the majority of claims. However, for&nbsp;<a href="https://www.kingsbridge.co.uk/policy-documents/">section 10</a>&nbsp;on your policy there is a 4-year extended reporting period for you to notify us of a claim for an investigation during the period your policy was active</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">. Any claim in these sections must be notified to insurers within 30 days of an insured event taking place and before any response to HMRC. Your appointed representation will work with you to respond and manage communications with HMRC.<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br><i>(Use for Cyber Liability)&nbsp;</i></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Cyber Liability cover operates on a ‘claims made’ basis and therefore the policy must be live in order to respond in the majority of claims. For some sections of the cover however, you can notify us of a claim up to 30 days following your policy expiry date</span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">. Please see your&nbsp;<a href="https://www.kingsbridge.co.uk/policy-documents/">policy wording</a>&nbsp;for full details<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>Whether you’re currently insured with Kingsbridge or not, our customer service team is always here to help. Please don’t hesitate to reply to this email if you need any further information on any of the above.<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>Kind regards,<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>{!User.FirstName}<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Customer Service Team<br></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br>E:&nbsp;</span><a href="mailto:customersupport@kingsbridge.co.uk" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12pt;">customersupport@kingsbridge.co.uk</a><br><span style="font-size: 12pt;">T: 01242 808 740</span></div></div></div></div></div></div>]]></td>
</tr>
</table>